What's in this directory?

HOLDoc is a system for automatically typesetting HOL scripts, and
LaTeX documents with interspersed HOL text.

Documentation:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
holdoc-guide.txt                explains how it all works.


Programs:
~~~~~~~~~

hol_to_latex                    }
lts_to_latex                    } - see below
mng_to_latex                    }

extractDatatypes                a helper Perl script to build .imn
                                files from *Theory.sig files.  It
                                identifies types, constructors, and
                                fields from Hol_datatype-defined
                                datatypes.

extractDefinitions              a helper Perl script to build .imn
                                files from *Theory.sig files.  It
                                identifies auxiliary functions from
                                Define-defined constants.


Source code:
~~~~~~~~~~~~

Makefile                        makefile to build all the programs

hol_to_latex.ml                 render HOL into LaTeX (not fully working)
lts_to_latex.ml                 render HOL-encoded labelled transition system into LaTeX
mng_to_latex.ml                 render LaTeX with embedded HOL (extension .mng) into LaTeX

simpledump.ml                   debugging: dump tokens scanned to stdout
simpletexdump.ml                debugging: dump TeXed tokens to stdout

holdoc_munge.ml and .mli        main module: do all the work
hollex.mll and .mli             lexer: lexing the HOL or LaTeX source.
holdoc_init.ml and .mli         init module: reading the init (.imn) files


TeXery:
~~~~~~~

ltsmunge.sty                    style to be included by LaTeX files using mng_to_latex

leftdisplay.sty                 style file required by ltsmunge.sty
prooftree.tex                   style file required by lts_to_latex
t1bchx.fd                       font file (maybe) required by ltsmunge.sty
t1bchy.fd                       font file (maybe) required by ltsmunge.sty

hostlts.tex                     hardwired wrapper for the LTS resulting from lts_to_latex

llncs.cls                       class file here for convenience


That's all, folks!

--KW 8-)
